Initialize wasi-libc cwd from the process PWD environment lazily.

The earlier constructor-based approach was unreliable for archive-linked WASI
programs. The constructor object was often omitted entirely, so child
processes still started with `__wasilibc_cwd = "/"` even though the runtime
passed `PWD=/some/path`.

Move cwd initialization into `getcwd.c`, which already owns the cwd storage,
and expose `__wasilibc_ensure_cwd()` so `chdir()` and other cwd-sensitive
paths can force initialization before touching `__wasilibc_cwd`.

